subSubSection.paragraph:
[Japanese name: Ibo-kagi-namako (Iwami and other Japanese form); and Sado-nadeshiko-namako (Sado form)] (
Figs 2–10
)

paragraph.treatmentCitationGroup:
Chirodota japonica Marenzeller, 1882: 123–124
;
Lampert 1885: 236
;
Théel 1886: 17
, 33, pl. II, fig. 3.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
In the Iwami form, living body color deep red, with tentacles white, and color gradually fades during preservation (
Fig. 2A–E
). Living body color of small specimens paler than that of large specimens. Mouth and anus terminal. Numerous “hook papillae” present in inter-radius of both dorsal and ventral body skin, through anterior to posterior, low hemisphere form (preserved and living specimens). Color of papillae surfaces (preserved and living specimens) deeper than adjacent body skin. Wheel-papillae absent. Body color of living state white semitransparent to whitish pink in Sado form, with numerous pale-red minute spots with tentacles white (
Fig. 7
).
